m talking about. Like any good bubble, it&#8217;s participatory.</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">People will feel like they can actually fix the government, so t=
hey&#8217;ll put more effort into actually trying to fix the government. Th=
at might come in the form of submitting ideas, and it might come in the for=
m of calling their Congresspeople to push them to enact DOGE&#8217;s recomm=
endations.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The involvement of the people will ma=
ke it more likely that DOGE succeeds in streamlining the machine, which mak=
es it easier for entrepreneurs to start companies assuming the machine will=
 be fixed, which means more people will try to start companies to fix probl=
ems that they see.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Whether this is exactly=
 how it plays out or not is of secondary importance. In forming the bubble,=
 the important part is that people </span><em>believe </em><span>this is ho=
w it will play out, which shapes their actions.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">Those things feel squishy, but they&#8217;re real. They can turn int=
o a self-fulfilling prophecy.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I guess one reason=
 I&#8217;m writing this is so that you feel a little of the FOMO yourself, =
so that we can all work on this American project together. Bubbles work bes=
t when they grow.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Whoever you voted for and howe=
ver you feel about the results of the election, there is now a clear choice=
: you can spend your time wallowing and miss out on what may be the greates=
t opportunity to build in America since the Second Industrial Revolution, o=
r you can get to work and build.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That&#8217;s an=
other thing that&#8217;s surprised me, just how non-partisan this feels. Th=
e line is not Democrat vs. Republican, but those who think the American peo=
ple can make America, and the world, better and those who think we need gov=
ernment bureaucracy to do it for us.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To wh=
it, in response to the DOGE announcement, Box CEO Aaron Levie, who vocally =
supported Kamala, </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/ccea1aa2-=
d72d-46d8-9873-548d02f454a3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: =
underline;">tweeted last night</a><span>: &#8220;There&#8217;s significant =
opportunity to make the government more capable of delivering for Americans=
, and ironically it will actually cost less not more.&#8221;</span></p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Earlier in the day, he </span><a href=3D"https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/7dcc7a83-3560-4794-9e87-0f9cee671c87?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ=
=2Egb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m=
8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); text-decoration: underline;">tweeted</a><span>, &#8220;America coul=
d enter a supercycle of growth in manufacturing, energy, housing, innovatio=
n, and more with the right policies going forward.&#8221;</span></p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">Whatever bitterness and divisions people feel, I think it&#8217;=
s time to let them go. This is bigger than politics.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">No one likes paying more taxes to fund wasteful bureaucracy. No one li=
kes feeling like their country is broken and there&#8217;s nothing they can=
 do about it. No one likes things going 100x more slowly than they should o=
r costing 100x more than they should. We can all agree on a lot.&#160;</p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">The American machine, for all its flaws, is the best the w=
orld has built so far, and we&#8217;ve never had a better chance to make it=
 run even better. The ramifications if we do &#8211; cheaper energy, better=
 goods, faster travel, more potent drugs, and much, much more &#8211; benef=
it everyone.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This is a meta-bubble that could sp=
awn inflection bubbles for decades to come.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><str=
ong><span>Welcome to the Trump Bubble. The </span><a href=3D"https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/a633f2ed-85d3-42b7-8eac-42a5879fc769?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ=
